<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="236" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,1394,1489]" box="[160,294,1394,1420]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,1394,1420]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,1394,1489]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,407,1428,1454]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,247,1428,1454]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[269,391,1428,1454]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Figure 2a</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[580,687,1429,1454]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.30 mm</quantity>
, sparsely setose. Head, mesosoma and metasoma reddish brown. Antenna, mandibles, wing venation and legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1155,1548,1678]" lastBlockId="9.[160,1156,142,237]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="236" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,372,1548,1574]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,222,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[239,357,1548,1574]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Figure 2b</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Lateral and inferior area of face smooth, scattered setose; in frontal view with slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. Malar sulci simple. Antenna with 13 articles, filiform; F1 twice longer than F2; F2–F11 subequal in length; F4–F11 with rhinaria. Compound eyes glabrous. Occiput striated. Vertex smooth. 
<emphasis box="[938,1046,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Pronotal plate smooth. Medial bridge of pronotal plate narrow, with lateral foveae open and deep. Dorsal margin of pronotal plate straight. Pronotal carina absent. Sides of pronotum slightly striated and highly setose behind genae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1155,280,341]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,472,280,306]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,308,280,306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Mesoscutum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[324,458,280,306]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Figure 2a,c</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
In lateral view as long as wide; smooth and shining. Notauli absent. Parapsidal hair line present. Parascutal impression inconspicuous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,384,583]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,342,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Mesoscutellum.</emphasis>
Scutellar foveae at base sculptured, longer than broad. Lateral bars of scutellum striated with a small fovea beneath. Dorsal surface of scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1147,420,445]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Figure 2c</figureCitation>
) weakly sculptured, reticulate-areolate; posterior margin round. Scutellar plate (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1147,454,479]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Figure 2c</figureCitation>
) flat and smooth, not elevated above the scutellum, drop-shaped, covers 1/2 of scutellum in dorsal view; surface smooth without glandular pit; with a dark impression on the entire edge of scutellar plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,627,687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,318,627,653]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Mesopectum.</emphasis>
Mesopleuron striated; with mesopleural carina and precoxal carina conspicuous, without subalar pit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,731,826]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,549,731,757]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Metapectal-propodeal complex.</emphasis>
Metapleuron slightly striated; anteroventral cavity conspicuous; posterior margin raised and hairy. Propodeum elongate, setose except on the carinae; lateral propodeal carinae subparallel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,870,965]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,239,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Wings.</emphasis>
Fore wings highly setose, hyaline, apical margin with hair fringes quite long. Hairless towards the base of wing. Marginal cell (
<figureCitation box="[722,829,905,930]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Figure 2a</figureCitation>
) completely open, elongate, three times longer than broad
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1157,1008,1069]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,221,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Legs.</emphasis>
Mid- and hind coxae with a patch of hairs dorsolateral and posterodorsal, respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1113,1173]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,429,1113,1139]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1113,1139]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[300,415,1113,1139]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1581,1604]" captionTargetBox="[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[205,1112,142,1564]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Hydrelliaeucoila rufa Reche sp. nov. A- Habitus; B- Head in frontal view; C- Mesosoma and scutellum in dorsal view, arrow indicates dark impression on the entire edge. D- Head in lateral view, arrow indicated slightly dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. E- Head and mesosoma in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758283/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Figure 2a</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Smooth and shining. Hairy ring at base of syntergum complete, woolly, with a weak row of long setae on each side posteriorly; distally smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1217,1277]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,277,1217,1243]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Variation.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[435,594,1217,1242]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.20–1.50 mm</quantity>
. Marginal cell twice or three times as long as wide. Hairy ring at base of syntergum complete or incomplete dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,356,1321,1347]" box="[160,356,1321,1347]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,225,1321,1347]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[160,777,1390,1416]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,777,1390,1416]" box="[160,777,1390,1416]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,291,1390,1416]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Etymology.</emphasis>
In reference to the colouring of the body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[160,442,1460,1486]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,442,1460,1486]" box="[160,442,1460,1486]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,254,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Biology.</emphasis>
Host unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="236" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1155,1529,1589]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,307,1529,1555]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Distribution.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[330,425,1530,1555]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1096,1119]" captionTargetBox="[165,1152,143,1078]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[163,1153,142,1079]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of Hydrelliaeucoila species from Argentina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758289/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[447,560,1530,1555]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. It is known only from Ensenada, 
<collectingRegion country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
. This distribution belongs to the Pampean province (Chacoan subregion).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[160,1156,1633,1728]" lastBlockId="10.[160,1156,142,410]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,293,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[309,540,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[309,540,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Hydrelliaeucoila rufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[553,645,1634,1659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the other two species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[228,342,1669,1694]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Argentina</collectingCountry>
by presenting the following combination of characters: head and mesosoma reddish brown (black in 
<taxonomicName box="[590,691,1703,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeria">
<emphasis box="[590,691,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">H. egeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[890,1037,1703,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[890,1037,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1050,1146,1703,1728]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); lateral and inferior area of face smooth (striated in 
<taxonomicName box="[747,845,142,167]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeria">
<emphasis box="[747,845,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">H. egeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); head in frontal view with carina adjacent to torulus (absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[590,734,177,202]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[590,734,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[745,837,177,202]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); medial bridge of pronotal plate narrow (broad in 
<taxonomicName box="[424,521,212,237]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeria">
<emphasis box="[424,521,212,237]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">H. egeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); with a dark impression on the entire edge of scutellar plate (without a dark impression on the entire edge in 
<taxonomicName box="[807,907,246,271]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeria">
<emphasis box="[807,907,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">H. egeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[969,1114,246,271]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[969,1114,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="10" pageNumber="237" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
